Northmoor Families...let's show some appreciation to our Northmoor faculty and staff with a video from our students. Two ways you can help:

1) Take a photo of your child/family with a thank you or we miss you sign/sidewalk chalk drawing.

2) Make a video recording with your child/family talking about why they love/miss Northmoor, appreciate their teachers, etc.

BE CREATIVE!!!

Send your submission via email to mhibbard@northmontschools.net
No later than Thursday April 23.
All videos and photos will be made into a presentation and posted for everyone to see.

Thanks in advance for your help...WE ARE NORTHMOOR!

post_text:
Today is our full-scale evacuation drill at Northmoor. All school buildings in the state of Ohio are required to perform three safety drills of varying types during a three year period. This safety drill will include students and staff leaving the school grounds for a brief time. We will be walking to a safe location off-site and then returning to Northmoor.

The safety drill should only last about one hour. Students will remain under the supervision of their teacher and Northmont staff throughout the entire experience. Please avoid scheduling any appointments or early dismissals.

Northmont is very sensitive to the fact that we are trying to provide important and mandated safety training…

Open houses will be held at each elementary during the week of July 23-25. Check our website for updates throughout this summer, and see current information listed below:

ENROLLMENT PACKETS for the 2019-2020 School Year are now available at the Front Desk of the Kleptz YMCA, and at the Northmont District office at 4001 Old Salem Rd.

The packet MUST be completed in full and returned before your child is considered…

post_text:
Hello!! This Monday, June 3rd, Northmoor PTO will be hosting a donation drive for FISH.
From 10 am-2 pm at Northmoor Elementary, we will be accepting hygiene products (shampoo, conditioner, deodorant etc.), any and all cleaning items, paper products (toilet paper, paper towels, paper plates etc.), food that does not have to be refrigerated and/or easily cooked, we will also be accepting coloring books/crayons and/or small toys. If you cannot make it but would like to donate please contact Diane Schneider, Cara Brandell, Lori Lynn or Becky Killion Johnson, or email the PTO at ptonorthmoor@gmail.com. Thank you all!
